<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-04T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-04T09:00:00-05:00" n="776" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d776">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">821.24/8–2844: Airgram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lane</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-04T10:00:00-04:00">September
                                    4, 1944—10 a.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>A–598. Reference the last paragraph of the Embassy’s despatch no. 3806 of
                            May 20, 1944 and the Embassy’s telegram 1509, August 28, 7 p.m., it does
                            not appear that the detailed information you request would be useful for
                            the purpose you indicate, since for your secret information, the total
                            figure in the lend-lease agreement and the sum total of actual
                            deliveries is larger for the other country.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>